  "text": "The Grafana Loki client implementation in pkg/components/loki/ contains timeout and retry/backoff configuration across two distinct client types:\n\nHTTP CLIENT (lokihttp package):\n- pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/config.go defines the Config struct with Timeout (time.Duration) and BackoffConfig (backoff.Config) fields that control HTTP client behavior.\n- pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/client.go implements the HTTP client with:\n  * Client interface defining Stop() and StopNow() methods (line 121)\n  * newClient() function that sets c.client.Timeout = cfg.Timeout (line 175)\n  * sendBatch() function (line 290) that creates a backoff instance with backoff.New(c.ctx, c.cfg.BackoffConfig) (line 299), implements retry logic with backoff.Wait() (line 315), and checks backoff.Ongoing() (line 318) to determine retry continuation\n  * StopNow() method (line 376) that cancels the context to stop retrying HTTP requests\n- pkg/components/loki/lokihttp/fake.go provides a Fake client implementation with a StopNow() stub method (line 39) for testing.\n\nGRPC CLIENT (lokigrpc package):\n- pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/config.go defines the Config struct with Timeout (time.Duration) and Retries (uint) fields.\n- pkg/components/loki/lokigrpc/client.go implements the gRPC client with:\n  * NewClient() factory function that initializes the gRPC connection (line 25)\n  * grpcRetryOption() method (line 82) that configures retry behavior using grpc.WithUnaryInterceptor() and grpcretry.UnaryClientInterceptor() with grpcretry.WithMax(c.cfg.Retries) (line 85)\n  * timeoutCtx() method (line 90) that creates a context with timeout using context.WithTimeout(context.Background(), c.cfg.Timeout) when Timeout > 0 (line 92)\n\nThese files work together to provide configurable timeout and retry mechanisms for both HTTP and gRPC-based communication with Loki backends."
}

